docs.text: " a breed apart " casts rutger hauer as a crazy , bird-loving recluse who picks his feathered friends over kathleen turner .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a bit hard to swallow ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: that's only the first of many improbabilities in this film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: hauer stars as a man obsessed with keeping the birds on his island safe , while boothe plays a guy hired to steal a couple of rare eagle eggs by a rich egg collector .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: turner is the woman caught between the two men .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " a breed apart " isn't a bad movie , exactly .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: indeed , i found myself rooting for both the hauer and boothe characters , even though their goals couldn't be more different .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the problem with the film is that there are just too many inconsistencies .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for example , early on in the film , hauer physically assaults two drunken rednecks shooting at " his " birds .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: later on , the rednecks come back for revenge with four other people , and hauer kills a few of them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i have a tough time believing that the police wouldn't get involved at that point .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: another problem is the silly love-triangle that develops .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i didn't care one way or the other who ended up with turner .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i was more interested in finding out which of the two men would be victorious in their respective missions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , despite this uninteresting sub-plot , turner did manage to give a great performance as the woman who reminds the two men that sometimes there's more to life than money and birds .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as for hauer , he's an actor i've always admired .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he has a penchant for picking strange and unusual characters .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and this one is no exception .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he's frequently seen riding around his island on a white horse , wearing pirate's clothing , and holstering a cross-bow .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: despite all his eccentric mannerisms , though , hauer always manages to let the human side of his character shine through .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for example , there's a scene in which he barks at turner and her son because they came onto his island a day early .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he comes off as crazy loner in that scene , but a few minutes later , he is apologizing to turner , and we believe his intentions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: soon after , we find out he's a vietnam vet , and his actions become fairly clear to us .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " a breed apart " isn't a great movie by any means , but it does contain good performances by all three leads , and it's worth seeing for that reason alone .
docs.label: positive
